mus, and approached the Turkish camp, which had been pitched, upon a vast and elevated table-ground, commanded on all sides by superior heights, which, however, were fortified and well-garrisoned by Janissaries.  The Epirots halted, and immediately prepar
ed to raise their tents, while their commander, attended by a few of his officers, instantly proceeded to the pavilion of Karam Bey.
