 spirit.  We must forget these things, we must forget.  Epirus! he is not a patriot who can spare a thought from thee.  And yet, so young, so beautiful, so gifted, so worthy of a hero! when I saw her by her great father's side, sharing his toils, aiding h
is councils, supplying his necessities, methought I gazed upon a ministering angel! upon -- "
