 last and highest chain of mountains and reaching the summit by dawn.  The cheerful light of morning revealed to them the happy plains of a Christian country.  With joyful spirits they descended into the fertile land, and stopped at a beautiful Greek vill
age, embowered in orchards and groves of olive-trees.
