\par }\pard \qc \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\tx900\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\cgrid0 \page }{\b\f1\cgrid0 CHAPTER 18
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\tx900\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\cgrid0 
\par 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\b\f1\fs20\cf6\cgrid0 \hich\af1\dbch\af0\loch\f1 18.\hich\f1 \'b6\loch\f1 1\tab}}\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\tx900{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls18\pnrnot0\pndec\pnb1\pni0\pncf6\pnf1\pnfs20\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnsp120 {\pntxtb 18.\'b6}}
\faauto\ls18\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\cgrid0 Three or four days passed away at the castle of Justinian, in  which Nic\'e6
us used his utmost exertions to divert the anxiety of Iduna.  One day was spent in examining the castle, on another he amused her with a hawking party, on a third he carried her to the neighbouring ruins of a temple, and read his favourite \'c6
schylus to her amid its lone and elegant columns.  It was impossible for any one to be more amiable and entertaining, and Iduna could not resist recognising his many virtues and accomplishments.  The courier had not yet returned from Croia, which Nic\'e6
us accounted for by many satisfactory reasons.  The suspense, however, at length became so painful to Iduna, that she proposed to the Prince of Athens that they should, without further delay, proceed to that city.    As usual, Nic\'e6
us was not wanting in many plausible arguments in favour of their remaining at the castle, but Iduna was resolute.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\tx900{\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\cgrid0 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\b\f1\fs20\cf6\cgrid0 \hich\af1\dbch\af0\loch\f1 18.\hich\f1 \'b6\loch\f1 2\tab}}\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\tx900{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls18\pnrnot0\pndec\pnb1\pni0\pncf6\pnf1\pnfs20\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnsp120 {\pntxtb 18.\'b6}}
\faauto\ls18\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\cgrid0 "Indeed, dear Nic\'e6us," she said, "my anxiety to see my father, or hear from him, is so great, that there is scar
cely any danger which I would not encounter to gratify my wish.  I feel that I have already taxed your endurance too much.  But we are no longer in a hostile land, and guards and guides are to be engaged. Let me then depart alone!"
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\tx900{\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\cgrid0 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\b\f1\fs20\cf6\cgrid0 \hich\af1\dbch\af0\loch\f1 18.\hich\f1 \'b6\loch\f1 3\tab}}\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\tx900{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls18\pnrnot0\pndec\pnb1\pni0\pncf6\pnf1\pnfs20\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnsp120 {\pntxtb 18.\'b6}}
\faauto\ls18\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\cgrid0 "Iduna!" exclaimed Nic\'e6us, reproachfully.  "Alas! Iduna, you are cruel, but I did not expect this!"
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\tx900{\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\cgrid0 
