\faauto\ls18\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\cgrid0 "'Tis well," said Nic\'e6us.  "From the tower of the castle you may behold the waves of the Ionian Sea.  You will remain here a close prisoner, until one of my galleys arrive from Pir\'e6
us to bear us to Italy. 
 Mine you must be, Iduna.  It remains for you to decide under what circumstances.  Continue in your obstinacy, and you may bid farewell for ever to your country and to your father.  Be reasonable, and a destiny awaits you, which offers everything that has
 hitherto been considered the source or cause of happiness."  Thus speaking, the prince retired, leaving the Lady Iduna to her own unhappy thoughts.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\tx900\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\cgrid0 
