ardly dare to think, or even hope.  And yet forgiveness is a heavenly boon.  Perhaps the memory of old days may melt her.  As for yourself, sir -- but I'll not speak, I cannot.  Noble Iskander, if I mistake not, you may whisper words in that fair ear, les
s grating than my own.  May you be happy!  I will not profane your prospects with my vows.  And yet I'll say farewell!"
