hey were filled with astonishment and disquietude.  Events, however, gave them little opportunity to indulge in anxiety or grief.  On the day that Hunniades and his lances arrived at Croia, the invading army of the Turks under the Prince Mahomed crossed t
he mountains, and soon after pitched their camp on the fertile plain of Kallista.
