The night before the arrival of Iduna at the famous fountain, the Christian army had taken up its position within a few miles of the Turks.  The turbaned warriors wished to delay the engagement until the new moon, the eve of whic
h was at hand.  And it happened on that said eve that Iskander calling to mind his contract with the Turkish prince made in the gardens of the Seraglio at Adrianople, and believing from the superstitious character of Mahomed that he would not fail to be a
t the appointed spot, resolved, as we have seen, to repair to the fountain of Kallista.
